</div> 
<p><strong>Law of Causality</strong> is an <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Incantations" href="/Incantations" target="">Incantation</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The&nbsp;Law of Causality spell&nbsp;serves as a counter-offensive after receiving multiple hits. Updated to&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a>.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>One of the incantations of the Golden Order fundamentalists.</em><br><em>One of the key fundamentals.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Manifests a small ring of causality within that allows the caster to</em><br><em>automatically retaliate upon receiving a certain number of blows.</em><br><br><em>The fundamentalists describe the Golden Order through the</em><br><em>powers of regression and causality. Causality is the pull between</em><br><em>meanings; that which links all things in a chain of relation</em><em>.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to find Law of Causality</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Given by&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Gideon Ofnir" href="/Gideon+Ofnir">Gideon Ofnir</a> after&nbsp;beating <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Mohg, Lord of Blood" href="/Mohg,+Lord+of+Blood">Mohg, Lord of Blood</a>&nbsp;and asking about the cocoon in the boss arena.</li> 
 <li>If not received from Gideon Ofnir, it can be purchased from&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Twin Maiden Husks" href="/Twin+Maiden+Husks" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Twin Maiden Husks</a> after defeating <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Maliketh, the Black Blade" href="/Maliketh,+the+Black+Blade" target="">Maliketh, the Black Blade</a>.</li> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Video Location" href="https://youtu.be/RGeo4anYcc4?t=3319">Video Location</a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Law of Causality Guide</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Golden Order Incantations" href="/Golden+Order+Incantations" target="">Golden Order Incantation</a></li> 
 <li>487 base holy attack that increases based on incant scaling</li> 
 <li>Stamina cost: 20</li> 
 <li>Deals holy damage</li> 
 <li>Triggers after receiving five hits.</li> 
 <li>The buff lasts for 120 seconds or until the explosion is triggered.</li> 
 <li>Only damaging hits will trigger the explosion. Damage-over-time effects, self-inflicted damage, and&nbsp;completely blocked attacks&nbsp;don't count.</li> 
 <li>Retaliates with a small area-of-effect explosion that can knock enemies back.</li> 
 <li>Since this incantation only has Intelligence requirement, a pure Int build with less than 10 Faith, which excludes them from using most Sacred Seals, can still use this incantation by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Frenzied Flame Seal" href="/Frenzied+Flame+Seal">Frenzied Flame Seal</a>.</li> 
 <li><span style="color: #ff6600;"><em>NOTE:</em></span>&nbsp;Since&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a>&nbsp;Duration has been extended from 60 to 120 seconds.</li> 
</ul> 
