				<li id="16590988" class="cmnt-root" data="40" data-d="1649066182000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578211/Law-of-Causality" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">04 Apr 2022 05:56</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16590988" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Okay from personal testing on a variety of tougher enemies using the golden order talisman with a spell buff of 335, Flock&apos;s Canvas talisman, and sacred scorpion charm, the damage this will do is bad. <br/>Against the knight outside Cathedral of Dragon Communion it did around 450-500 damage. Against the cleanrot knight outside Prayer Room at Haligtree it did about 250 as they are rather resistant to holy damage. Against the Aulbinaurics at Mohg&apos;s place it did once again around 500. <br/>In short the damage on this is really bad, and the range isn&apos;t great either. <br/>It also doesn&apos;t immediately trigger upon being hit 5 times, there is a delay. Which for faster weapons is enough for a sixth hit or to dodge.<br/>The only benefit it does have is that it does a rather good amount of poise damage. I&apos;m not sure how much, I haven&apos;t yet tested it on bosses, but enough to at least constantly break the guard of most enemies. <br/>I&apos;ve tested other sacred seals to see if it was perhaps a weird interaction, and found no actual difference, only dealing less damage in line with the lesser spell buff and no inherent buff from Golden Order seal. <br/>So yeah, either something is fundamently broken with the spell, or they really balanced it weirdly. I mean it still doesn&apos;t explain how Gideon can oneshot with it. Sure he&apos;s a boss, but he&apos;s doing regular player damage with the rest of his spells. At any rate it isn&apos;t really worth using. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16590988" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16590988" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">4</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>43</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>3</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16590988"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16590988" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16590988"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
